title: For Sale:  Collectible sister shotguns, Kimber Valier II 16 & 20 gauge Side by Sides
postcontent:
Hey there, 

     I have my fathers personal collected, very lightly used Kimber Valier Shotguns. I say personal collected because he was a Professional Wing Shooting guide in South Dakota and he was sponsored by Kimber. While guiding he used his demo guns, etc with his guests. These two were only used a few time during family and personal hunts, thus very lightly used. 

     Unfortunately he has recently passed away, and he wanted me to use find these two Sisters a home in order to helpay his final senses and debts. Together would be great but not necessary. 

     They were gradede a year and a half ago, right before coming out and suddenly slipping away. I don't have the exact terminology in front of me at the moment, but I know they were graded Excellent and have been cared for properly. Like I stated, they are Kimber Valier II  SxS 16 and 20 gauged. They both have the Blue coloring, case hardened steel, felt storage bags, custom leather and canvass cases. 

     They are fairly rare one the states. I believe they are made in Turkey. They are used by high end clientele and/or collected. If you are a collector then you know more than I most likely. If you are looking for a high end respectable shotgun to use or show off, etc. Do some research yourself. They are awesome. Luckily I son't need them and unfortunately I do need to sell them to cover his final expenses.. Thus here they are. 

     Last time they were looked over Professionally and graded, the Valued price placed on them was between $4199 - $4495 each. Now I know things change with time and location. Usually good, collectible guns increase in value. I have seen a bit of a range on these Models, although not many put there. The low seem to be offered by someone that either doesn't know what they've got or have used the heck out of them. And yes, there are some out there that apparently must also have solid gold plating!! Haha, I am not trying to take anyone and I am open to discussion. The realistic range that I have been researching and watching has been right in the ballpark of when last graded. I am just hoping to find a good home for these two sisters, if kept together, that be great but not necessary. Hopefully someone who can both enjoy some light use out of them and also enjoy having a great investment..! For the hunters, also have brand new top model Tri Tronics and RE Hunting/Shooting Sport glasses. I will provide pics, as much info, etc if you're interested. Old West attitude, can wheel and deal.

 Thank you for the look,

     In the Spirit of the West, J Mac
